 ],
 "segments": [
  {
   "start": 0.0,
   "end": 3.32,
   "text": " There's a company that makes more money per employee than almost anyone on earth,"
  },
  {
   "start": 3.76,
   "end": 8.4,
   "text": " around 100 staff, billions in annual profit, and the entire business model is this."
  },
  {
   "start": 8.86,
   "end": 12.76,
   "text": " You give them a dollar, they hand you a token, and they keep the dollar, that's Tether,"
  },
  {
   "start": 12.98,
   "end": 14.08,
   "text": " and it's completely legal."
  },
  {
   "start": 14.56,
   "end": 17.46,
   "text": " Here's why it might be the most genius business model ever invented."
  },
  {
   "start": 17.88,
   "end": 20.06,
   "text": " Tether runs USDT, a stablecoin."
  },
  {
   "start": 20.54,
   "end": 23.44,
   "text": " One USDT is always meant to equal one US dollar."
  },
  {
   "start": 23.94,
   "end": 27.38,
   "text": " Crypto traders love it, it's a dollar that lives on the blockchain so they can"
  },
  {
   "start": 27.38,
   "end": 29.0,
   "text": " jump in and out of trades instantly."
  },
  {
   "start": 29.72,
   "end": 32.96,
   "text": " To get one, you hand Tether a real dollar, and they mint you a token."
  },
  {
   "start": 33.34,
   "end": 36.96,
   "text": " Simple, but the magic isn't the token, it's what happens to your dollar."
  },
  {
   "start": 37.4,
   "end": 39.64,
   "text": " Because Tether doesn't just let your dollar sit in a drawer,"
  },
  {
   "start": 40.02,
   "end": 43.36,
   "text": " it takes all those billions in parks, the mostly in US treasury bills."
  },
  {
   "start": 43.84,
   "end": 48.02,
   "text": " Basically the safest loan on the planet, earning around 4-5% a year."
  },
  {
   "start": 48.46,
   "end": 51.68,
   "text": " And how much of that interest do they pass back to you, the token holder?"
  },
  {
   "start": 52.12,
   "end": 54.7,
   "text": " Zero, you're holding a dollar that pays you nothing, and"
  },
  {
   "start": 54.7,
   "end": 56.3,
   "text": " Tether keeps every cent of the yield."
  },
  {
   "start": 56.3,
   "end": 57.66,
   "text": " Now multiply it."
  },
  {
   "start": 57.96,
   "end": 61.02,
   "text": " There's well over 100 billion dollars of USDT out there,"
  },
  {
   "start": 61.24,
   "end": 65.28,
   "text": " which means well over 100 billion of other people's money working for Tether, for free."
  },
  {
   "start": 65.76,
   "end": 69.54,
   "text": " And normally getting capital is expensive, a bank pays interest to its depositors,"
  },
  {
   "start": 69.94,
   "end": 73.1,
   "text": " a company pays interest on its bonds, everyone pays for money."
  },
  {
   "start": 73.72,
   "end": 74.18,
   "text": " Tether's cost?"
  },
  {
   "start": 74.62,
   "end": 77.06,
   "text": " Nothing, it's an interest free loan from millions of users."
  },
  {
   "start": 77.62,
   "end": 79.4,
   "text": " And it keeps 100% of the return."
  },
  {
   "start": 79.9,
   "end": 83.86,
   "text": " In 2024, the company reported around 13 billion dollars in profit,"
  },
  {
   "start": 83.86,
   "end": 85.9,
   "text": " with a team you could fit in a single room."
  },
  {
   "start": 86.42,
   "end": 87.14,
   "text": " So what's the catch?"
  },
  {
   "start": 88.12,
   "end": 91.7,
   "text": " Trust, the whole thing holds up only as long as people believe every token is"
  },
  {
   "start": 91.7,
   "end": 95.14,
   "text": " really backed by a real dollar, and don't all rush to cash out at once."
  },
  {
   "start": 95.88,
   "end": 99.28,
   "text": " Tether has been fine before for overstating what was actually in its reserves,"
  },
  {
   "start": 99.7,
   "end": 102.84,
   "text": " and it publishes attestations, not full independent audits."
  },
  {
   "start": 103.22,
